&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Founded by former Workday clients, we value partnership and engagement as a cornerstone of our business. With years of functional and technical experience in all phases of Workday&#39;s deployment life cycle, we can determine the most efficient integration designs and rapid deployment strategies. We develop maintainable solutions and provide support for integration testing and updates for new Workday releases.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Strategic Account Manager (SAM) is responsible for customer account management focused on revenue generation and opportunity pursuit. The SAM will be responsible for managing a regional portfolio of engaged customers, with a focus on driving new sales expansion through upsells and add-ons within the AMS customer base service offerings. They will collaborate with internal teams to identify and pursue sales opportunities, negotiate, and close deals. The role also involves maintaining relationships with AMS customers and partnering with Workday RSD and CBAEs to ensure customer needs are met. Additionally, the SAM will represent the company at regional Workday events to foster engagement and business growth.&amp;nbsp; Additionally, this role relies heavily on personal accountability for results, and a willingness to go ‘the extra mile’ for each and every customer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This remote role can be located anywhere within the U.S. to perform the required responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY EXPECTATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own new sales expansion within AMS (upsells &amp;amp;&amp;nbsp; add ons)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, leading scope pursuit using Sales Solution Architect, negotiate, and close deals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pass Extend/BOW, Competitive, or Ramp to Prime opportunities to Business Development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain relationships with AMS customers and associated Workday RSD &amp;amp; CBAE&#39;s to uncover expansion opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align with AMS Client Contact (ACC) to stay updated on customer needs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend Workday events within the region&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manages a high volume of multiple customers using exceptional organizational and time management techniques&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay on top of any major changes within their customer’s organization to be able to effectively help align service offerings based on evolving needs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand how the customer’s Workday roadmap can / will influence decisions and activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate clearly and concisely. Collaborate effectively and synergistically within designated teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working closely with Workday CBAEs to educate on Intecrowd capabilities and to partner on expansion opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal teams including: ACCs, Sales, AMS team and PS leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to “read the room” (virtually or in person) and pivot as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DESIRED SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous sales or business development experience in the Workday ecosystem is a MUST&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of consistently achieving team sales goals such as opening &amp;amp; closing opportunities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven account management / strategic planning experience, with demonstrated ability to support multiple customers effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to engage at the C-Level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to engage across corporate functions (AMS, Managing Professional Services, Executive Leadership, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You live by a set of values that align with the Values and Guiding Principles of our Charter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Founded by former Workday clients, we value partnership and engagement as a cornerstone of our business. With years of functional and technical experience in all phases of Workday&#39;s deployment life cycle, we can determine the most efficient integration designs and rapid deployment strategies. We develop maintainable solutions and provide support for integration testing and updates for new Workday releases.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Workday AI Transformation Practice Leader to define and scale our AI strategy across our Workday practice. This role is responsible for shaping how AI is leveraged across our business—including go-to-market strategy, delivery enablement, internal productivity, and client advisory services. This is not a role focused on configuring AI within Workday. Instead, this leader will drive how we integrate AI into our ways of working, leverage the broader ecosystem, and position AI as a core differentiator in how we sell and deliver Workday services. The ideal candidate will combine Workday expertise, consulting leadership, and practical AI application to deliver measurable impact across both client outcomes and internal efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Practice Strategy &amp;amp; Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and lead the AI Transformation strategy for the Workday practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify high-impact opportunities to apply AI across sales, delivery, and internal operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish a roadmap for AI-enabled capabilities and offerings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales &amp;amp; Go-To-Market Enablement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with sales and leadership to position AI in client conversations, proposals, and demos&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop AI-driven offerings and accelerators that enhance our Workday services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support pursuits by translating AI capabilities into clear business value for clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise clients on how to leverage AI within the Workday ecosystem and partner landscape, including tools such as:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Workday Sana&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paradox&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HiredScore&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evisort&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Capability &amp;amp; Delivery Enablement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and scale AI-enabled delivery capabilities, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automation of repetitive consulting tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI-assisted documentation, testing, and analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intelligent insights and reporting enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and implement tools that enhance delivery efficiency, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flowise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pipedream&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with functional and technical leaders to embed AI into real delivery workflows, not just isolated use cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal AI Adoption &amp;amp; Efficiency&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive adoption of AI tools across the organization to improve:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consultant productivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivery speed and quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge sharing and reuse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and lead AI enablement programs, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training and upskilling initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Best practices and governance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible AI usage guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to streamline internal processes using AI (e.g., staffing, forecasting, documentation, reporting)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ecosystem &amp;amp; Innovation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
